There is no build-in Checkstyle rules for that. However, for method arguments/parameters alignment you can use lib with additional checks for checkstyle - [check-tfij-style][1].

**1. Add lib to your `maven-checkstyle-plugin` (works with Gradle too) as a dependency, e.g.:**

```xml
&lt;plugin&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-checkstyle-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;3.2.0&lt;/version&gt;
    &lt;configuration&gt;
        &lt;configLocation&gt;src/main/resources/checkstyle.xml&lt;/configLocation&gt;
        &lt;encoding&gt;UTF-8&lt;/encoding&gt;
        &lt;consoleOutput&gt;true&lt;/consoleOutput&gt;
        &lt;failsOnError&gt;true&lt;/failsOnError&gt;
        &lt;linkXRef&gt;false&lt;/linkXRef&gt;
    &lt;/configuration&gt;
    &lt;executions&gt;
        &lt;execution&gt;
            &lt;id&gt;validate&lt;/id&gt;
            &lt;phase&gt;validate&lt;/phase&gt;
            &lt;goals&gt;
                &lt;goal&gt;check&lt;/goal&gt;
            &lt;/goals&gt;
        &lt;/execution&gt;
    &lt;/executions&gt;
    &lt;dependencies&gt;
        &lt;dependency&gt;
            &lt;groupId&gt;pl.tfij&lt;/groupId&gt;
            &lt;artifactId&gt;check-tfij-style&lt;/artifactId&gt;
            &lt;version&gt;1.3.0&lt;/version&gt;
        &lt;/dependency&gt;
    &lt;/dependencies&gt;
&lt;/plugin&gt;
```

**2. Configure your checkstyle checks, e.g.:**

```xml
  &lt;module name=&quot;TreeWalker&quot;&gt;
    &lt;module name=&quot;MethodParameterAlignment&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;module name=&quot;MethodParameterLinesCheck&quot;&gt;
      &lt;property name=&quot;allowSingleLine&quot; value=&quot;false&quot;/&gt;
    &lt;/module&gt;
  &lt;/module&gt;
```

**Notice**

The lib contains more useful checks. Read the readme file for more details - [check-tfij-style][1].



  [1]: https://github.com/tfij/check-tfij-style

